  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">PARC Emergency Response to Winter Storm</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">PARC will enhance resilience and reduce disaster risk for 1000 families (6000 persons) through the provision of plastic sheets and blankets for use during winter. Priority of selection will be given to female-headed households and families including persons with disabilities, elders, or children. Based on the results of the damage assessment conducted by PARC , the targeted areas will be Khan Younis (Al-Zanna &#x2013; Khoza&apos;a &#x2013; WadiSalqa), Eastern Gaza (East of Shijaia and Sha&apos;af) and East of Beth Hanoon.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will bring about significant change to the lives of 6000 people living in Gaza who have been affected by the recent conflict by ensuring that they have the necessary materials (plastic sheets to limit water leakage from shelter roofs and 3 blankets per family) to mitigate the impacts of the winter storm until the end of winter.</narrative>
  </description>
